===Etymology===
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[ζύγωμα]]''' (''zygoma''), from '''[[ζυγόν]]''' (''zygon'') "anything which joins two", from '''[[ζυγώ]]''' (''zygo'') "to yoke, to join together".
